President Biden recently hosted a virtual Leaders Summit on Climate, where 40 world leaders came together to address the climate crisis. The United States and other nations announced ambitious climate targets, ensuring that countries responsible for half of the world's economy are committed to reducing emissions and limiting global warming to 1.5 degrees Celsius. The summit included discussions on raising climate ambition, investing in climate solutions, unleashing climate innovation, and the economic opportunities of climate action. Various announcements were made during the summit, including commitments to increase climate finance, promote clean technologies, and create job opportunities. The summit emphasized the need for urgent and collaborative action to combat climate change.